column10:
An interesting spin-off that takes place 17 years after the events of the previous installment and continues in a smaller version of the same map, which has been redesigned accordingly. This is a direct sequel with the continuation of the story of some characters and similar gameplay with some light RPG elements. It's not for everyone, and there are some inconsistencies and frustrating elements, but if you like post-apocalyptic settings, fun gunplay, and aren't tired of the Far Cry gameplay loop, give it a try.

Pros:
- Good optimization;
- Responsive controls;
- Cool expedition missions;
- Satisfying gunplay;
- Decent voice acting;
- Fun gameplay;
- Co-op;
- Good soundtrack;
- Cool weapon design;
- Very colorful visuals;
- Great sense of progression;
- Fun exploration;
- Decent AI;
- Cool buddy system;
- Good environmental storytelling;

Cons:
- Boring villains;
- Ubisoft Connect (Upaly) is unnecessary garbage;
- Most side missions are boring;
- Microtransactions;
- Many characters a little bit too out of whack;
- Gameplay loop can get very repetitive;

[h1]I would say yes, but with many caveats. Only worth it to complete the collection. [i]Runs thru Ubisoft launcher[/i].[/h1]

[b]I enjoyed the "transformed vibrant post-apocalyptic Hope County, Montana", despite everything felt like a reskin of Far Cry 5 with pink and blue chalk powder (map, weapons, gameplay mechanics).[/b]

[b](+)[/b] Carmina Rye and Timber;
[b](+)[/b] Basic player customization and skins;
[b](+)[/b] The upgradable home base is an unique feature here (along with a mode called "Expeditions");


[b](-)[/b][spoiler] Can't kill Joseph again >.<[/spoiler]
[b](-)[/b] Guns for Hire are pretty useless (I liked Carmina and later on The Judge, but Timber [i]the dog[/i] is the best -_-); I miss Cheeseburger and Peaches ToT and my faithful owl from Primal
[b](-)[/b] Terrible UI;
[b](-)[/b] Paltriest enemy ever: The Twins;
[b](-)[/b] Weak plot;
[b](-)[/b] Copy + Paste of many gameplay mechanics: repetitive finding treasures and resources, hunting, liberating outposts, etc.;
[b](-)[/b] It's nonsense how Far Cry series handle guns: why can't I add/remove a suppressor on a gun instead of buying (or crafting) a new one? The same goes for scopes and laser sights. :facepalm:


It is part of the FC series as well as could be a DLC for FC5 and no one would complain about it.
It is short, it is fun and I am glad I have it and had fun playing it (not as much as its predecessors, for sure).

[b]7.0/10.[b]
